<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Mac App Store variant of Release.entitlements (T10 Phase 1). Mirrors the direct-distribution Release
  entitlements with TWO removals:
    • `com.apple.security.temporary-exception.mach-lookup.global-name` — the `-spks`/`-spki` Sparkle
      installer XPC services (SUEnableInstallerLauncherService). The MAS build links no Sparkle, so those
      XPC names don't exist; App Review also flags temporary-exception entitlements.
    • `com.apple.developer.aps-environment` — the app NEVER registers for remote/push notifications (the
      daily reminder uses LOCAL UNUserNotificationCenter only, via capture_native), so the push
      entitlement is spurious. A `development` APS value in a store build is an upload/review risk, so
      dropping it is correct (local notifications need no entitlement).
  Everything else mirrors the known-good direct build: App Sandbox, network client, user-selected file
  access, the Google Sign-In keychain group. The ⌥E global hotkey uses Carbon RegisterEventHotKey
  (HotKeyController.swift) — sandbox-safe, no extra entitlement, no Accessibility/Input-Monitoring. Screen
  capture uses the user-granted Screen Recording permission (no entitlement). Applied by
  scripts/macos/build_mas.sh, which archives the stock Release configuration with CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS
  overridden to this file (there is no separate Release-MAS build configuration).

  ADDED for the App Store build only: `com.apple.developer.applesignin` — Sign in with Apple. Guideline
  4.8 requires offering it alongside Google on the store build, and the MAS provisioning profile permits
  the entitlement (Developer ID profiles forbid it, which is why the direct Release.entitlements omits
  it). The shared SignInPanel shows "Continue with Apple" when `isMacAppStoreBuild()` is true. Requires
  the Sign in with Apple capability on the com.capecho.app App ID (already enabled for iOS).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.applesignin</key>
	<array>
		<string>Default</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<true/>
	<key>keychain-access-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)com.google.GIDSignIn</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
